p: With regards to the proximate composition, high dietary inclusion levels (up to 50%) of TM larva meal did not lead to any changes in the moisture, protein or ash content in shrimp muscle [ 85] and rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss) fillets (raw and cooked) [ 82]. However, increased DM and EE contents of trout dorsal fillets were observed by Renna et al. [ 18] in fish fed the highest level (40%) of HI larva meal inclusion in their diets when compared to 20% HI- and FM-fed groups. Furthermore, Zhou et al. [ 45] reported no significant effects related to dietary HI larva meal utilization on the whole body composition of carp. Similarly, Belghit et al. [ 14] observed no changes in the whole body composition of HI-fed Atlantic salmon.
